{"type":"message-part","timestamp":"2026-06-16T03:07:15.440Z","messageId":"160853d8-ed24-4a63-b195-21c2c1e743b2","role":"user","index":1,"part":{"type":"text","text":"# Add Capacitor v8 Native Platform Packages\n\n## Background\n\nYou are working on a Vite + TypeScript web project that has already been initialized with Capacitor v8 core. The project at `/home/user/myapp` was bootstrapped with `@capacitor/core` and `@capacitor/cli` and the Capacitor configuration file (`capacitor.config.ts`) is already in place with `webDir` aligned to Vite's `dist` output. However, the native platform packages have NOT been installed yet, so commands that read the installed Capacitor platforms (such as `npx cap sync`) cannot operate against Android or iOS.\n\nYour job is to install the official Capacitor v8 Android and iOS NPM packages into the project so that the platform tooling is available. You do NOT need to run `npx cap add android` or `npx cap add ios` (that step requires native build toolchains that are out of scope here); only the NPM packages need to be present and a build + sync must succeed against the existing project.\n\n## Requirements\n\n* Install the official Android native platform package `@capacitor/android`.\n* Install the official iOS native platform package `@capacitor/ios`.\n* The versions installed for both packages MUST be compatible with Capacitor v8 (i.e., their major version must be `8`). Pick the latest 8.x release of each package.\n* After installation, building the web assets with `npm run build` must still succeed, and `npx cap sync` must complete with exit code 0 against the existing project.\n\n## Implementation Hints\n\n* Capacitor's official platform packages follow the same major version as `@capacitor/core` and `@capacitor/cli`. Use the npm tag/range that pins the major version to `8`.\n* The Capacitor CLI is invoked via `npx cap` and only reads installed platform packages from `node_modules`; you do not need to add or scaffold native project directories for this task.\n* Vite produces its build artifacts in `dist/`, which is already declared in `capacitor.config.ts` as `webDir`.\n* Use NPM's standard install command to add both packages as runtime `dependencies` and let NPM resolve to the latest 8.x version.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n* Project path: /home/user/myapp\n* `/home/user/myapp/package.json` must list BOTH `@capacitor/android` and `@capacitor/ios` in its `dependencies` section. The recorded version range for each MUST resolve to a Capacitor 8.x release (major version `8`).\n* `/home/user/myapp/node_modules/@capacitor/android/package.json` must exist, and its `version` field must satisfy the Capacitor 8.x major (i.e., its parsed major version is `8`).\n* `/home/user/myapp/node_modules/@capacitor/ios/package.json` must exist, and its `version` field must satisfy the Capacitor 8.x major (i.e., its parsed major version is `8`).\n* Running `npm run build` inside `/home/user/myapp` must exit with code `0`, and after the build, `/home/user/myapp/dist/index.html` must exist.\n* Running `npx cap sync` inside `/home/user/myapp` (after the build) must exit with code `0`."}}
